---------------------------------------
- Summary
---------------------------------------

A command-line tool to extract files from MPQ archives (used by Blizzard games).

Works on MacOS X and Linux.


---------------------------------------
- Compilation
---------------------------------------

somewhere$ mkdir build
somewhere$ cd build
build$ cmake <path/to/the/source/of/MPQExtractor>
build$ make

The executable will be put in build/bin/


---------------------------------------
- Usage
---------------------------------------

(See ./MPQExtractor --help for more details. All the examples below are shown
using the World of Warcraft 4.2 files, as of July 9th, 2011)

********

Retrieve the list of files in a MPQ archive:

$ ./MPQExtractor -l list.txt "/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/art.MPQ"
$ cat list.txt
art-md5.lst
Cameras\Abyssal_Maw_CameraFly_01.M2
Cameras\Abyssal_Maw_CameraFly_0100.skin
Cameras\FlyBy_Maelstrom.M2
Cameras\FlyBy_Maelstrom00.skin
Cameras\FlyByDwarf.m2
Cameras\FlyByDwarf00.skin
Cameras\FlyByGilneas_Telescope.M2
Cameras\FlyByGilneas_Telescope00.skin
Cameras\FlybyGilneasShort.M2
Cameras\FlybyGilneasShort00.skin
...

********

Search all the *.M2 files in a MPQ archive:

$ ./MPQExtractor -s *.M2 "/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/art.MPQ"
Opening '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/art.MPQ'...

Searching for '*.M2'...

Found files:
  - PARTICLES\LoginFX.m2
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMale.M2
  - Character\Worgen\Female\WorgenFemale.M2
  - Character\Goblin\Female\GoblinFemale.M2
  - Character\Draenei\Male\DraeneiMale.m2
  - Character\Draenei\Female\DraeneiFemale.m2
  - Character\Goblin\Male\GoblinMale.M2
....

********

Extract a specific file from a MPQ archive:

$ mkdir out
$ ./MPQExtractor -e "Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMale.M2" -o out "/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/art.MPQ"
Opening '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/art.MPQ'...

Extracting files...

$ ls out/
WorgenMale.M2

********

Extract some specific files from a MPQ archive, preserving the path hierarchy found inside the MPQ archive:

$ mkdir out
$ ./MPQExtractor -e "Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMale*" -f -o out "/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/art.MPQ"
Opening '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/art.MPQ'...

Searching for 'Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMale*'...

Found files:
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMale.M2
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleSkin00_03.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleSkin00_01.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleSkin00_05.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleNakedPelvisSkin00_05.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleSkin00_04.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleNakedPelvisSkin00_06.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleSkin00_06.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleSkin00_00.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleSkin00_02.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleSkin00_07.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleNakedPelvisSkin00_07.blp
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMale03.skin
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMale01.skin
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMale02.skin
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMale00.skin
  - Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMaleSkin00_05_Extra.blp
...

Extracting files...

$ ls out/Character/Worgen/Male/
WorgenMale.M2
WorgenMale00.skin
WorgenMale0060-00.anim
WorgenMale0060-01.anim
WorgenMale0061-00.anim
WorgenMale0062-00.anim
WorgenMale0064-00.anim
WorgenMale0065-00.anim
WorgenMale0066-00.anim
WorgenMale0067-00.anim
WorgenMale0068-00.anim
WorgenMale0069-00.anim
WorgenMale0069-01.anim
...

********

Apply some patches before extracting a specific file from a MPQ archive:

$ mkdir out
$ ./MPQExtractor -p /Applications/World\ of\ Warcraft/Data/wow-update-*.MPQ   \
                    /Applications/World\ of\ Warcraft/Data/wow-update-base-1*.MPQ  \
                    --prefix base -e "Character\Worgen\Male\WorgenMale.M2" -o out  \
                    "/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/art.MPQ"
Opening '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/art.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-13164.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-13205.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-13287.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-13329.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-13596.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-13623.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-base-13914.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-base-14007.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-base-14333.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-base-13914.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-base-14007.MPQ'...
Applying patch '/Applications/World of Warcraft/Data/wow-update-base-14333.MPQ'...

Extracting files...

$ ls out/
WorgenMale.M2


---------------------------------------
- Dependencies
---------------------------------------

The repository/package contain all the necessary files, no need to install anything.

The following libraries are used (and are part of the distribution):

  - StormLib (http://www.zezula.net/en/mpq/stormlib.html), no license, free to use
  - SimpleOpt 3.4 (http://code.jellycan.com/simpleopt/), MIT License


